    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends 👋, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change color of mui accordion in React js, you can use this code . It will change color of mui accordion in react js…","html":"<p>Hi Friends 👋,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change color of mui accordion in React js, you can use this code <code class=\"language-text\">sx={{color:'red'}}</code>. It will change color of mui accordion in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How change color of mui accordion in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui accordion in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI accordion.</li>\n<li>Define an inline css for the Accordion component.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI accordion.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Accordion<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> AccordionDetails<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> AccordionSummary<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Typography <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ExpandMoreIcon <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/icons-material/ExpandMore'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Define an inline css for the Accordion component.</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">accordion</code> component in your react js. For example, The accordion component is used to collapsible panels. and <code class=\"language-text\">color</code> CSS property set to <code class=\"language-text\">red</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Accordion\n    sx<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> \n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token string\">'red'</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material change color of mui accordion example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, to make border on mui in accordion, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">accordion</code> Component. You can use inline css style <code class=\"language-text\">sx={ color:'red'}}</code> and it will change color of mui accordion.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"> <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Accordion<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> AccordionDetails<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> AccordionSummary<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Typography <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ExpandMoreIcon <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/icons-material/ExpandMore'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">AccordionWithColor</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n     <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Accordion\n        sx<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> \n           <span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token string\">'red'</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n     <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n       <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>AccordionSummary\n         expandIcon<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ExpandMoreIcon <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n         aria<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>controls<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"panel1a-content\"</span>\n         id<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"panel1a-header\"</span>\n       <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n         <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Typography<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Accordion Title<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Typography<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n       <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>AccordionSummary<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n       <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>AccordionDetails<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n         <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Typography<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n           Accordion Content\n         <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Typography<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n       <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>AccordionDetails<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n     <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Accordion<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n   <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n <span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> AccordionWithColor<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and changed color of mui accordion in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/66be3/color-of-mui-accordion.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 13.924050632911392%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRkQAAABXRUJQVlA4IDgAAABQAwCdASoUAAMAPtFipk0oJiOiMAgBABoJZwAAW+ll+bkAAAD+8BuuQWrHxHw1I58Sz9ft+RoAAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, color, of, mui, accordion\"\n        title=\"React, color, of, mui, accordion\"\n        src=\"/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/8aab1/color-of-mui-accordion.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/81b7c/color-of-mui-accordion.webp 158w,\n/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/6ea66/color-of-mui-accordion.webp 315w,\n/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/8aab1/color-of-mui-accordion.webp 630w,\n/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/a70f5/color-of-mui-accordion.webp 945w,\n/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/4ef06/color-of-mui-accordion.webp 1260w,\n/static/895ee053335d9335af01e03a6ed57020/66be3/color-of-mui-accordion.webp 1362w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program change color of mui accordion in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=elated-haibt-ipd52l\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best 👍</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How change color of mui accordion in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"May 15, 2023","description":"Example of change color of mui accordion in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to change background color of mui accordion in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-05-15-how-change-background-color-of-mui-accordion-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui accordion always open in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-05-14-how-to-make-mui-accordion-always-open-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-05-15-how-change-color-of-mui-accordion-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-05-15-how-change-background-color-of-mui-accordion-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-05-14-how-to-make-mui-accordion-always-open-in-react-js/"}},
